HEADWORD: Kern baby
<hw>Kern baby</hw>. <def>A doll or image decorated with corn (grain)
flowers, etc., carried in the festivals of a kern, or harvest-home.
Called also <altname>harvest queen</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kerned</ent>⟦br⟧
